PREAMBLE

This software, including all its source code, object code, documentation, design
assets, database schemas, business logic, algorithms, data models, configuration
files, and all associated materials (collectively, the "Software") constitutes
highly valuable, confidential trade secrets and proprietary intellectual property
of MenuOS ("the Company"). The Software is protected by copyright law, trade
secret law, unfair competition law, and all applicable international intellectual
property treaties, including the Berne Convention, the TRIPS Agreement, and the
WIPO Copyright Treaty.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. DEFINITIONS

   1.1 "Software" means the MenuOS platform in its entirety, including but not
       limited to: all source code files, compiled binaries, scripts, database
       migrations, seed data, Supabase Edge Functions, configuration files,
       environment templates, design tokens, UI components, documentation,
       business logic, algorithms, data structures, and any derivative works
       created by the Company.

   1.2 "Authorized Personnel" means individuals who have been explicitly granted
       access in writing by the Company and who have executed a valid
       Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) and/or employment or contractor agreement
       with the Company that is currently in force.

   1.3 "Competing Product" means any software, service, or platform that provides
       substantially similar functionality to the Software, including but not
       limited to: QR-based digital menus, restaurant CRM systems, table ordering
       systems, kitchen display systems, or restaurant loyalty programs.

   1.4 "Derivative Work" means any work that is based upon, incorporates, or is
       derived from the Software or any portion thereof, including translations,
       adaptations, modifications, enhancements, ports, integrations, or any work
       that would be considered a derivative work under applicable copyright law.

   1.5 "Confidential Information" means the Software and all non-public
       information related to the Company's business, technology, customers,
       finances, strategies, and operations.

2. GRANT OF LICENSE — NO LICENSE GRANTED

   NO LICENSE OF ANY KIND IS GRANTED UNDER THIS AGREEMENT. Access to this
   repository and its contents is restricted exclusively to Authorized Personnel.
   Any access, use, or possession of the Software by any person or entity not
   qualifying as Authorized Personnel is unauthorized and constitutes
   misappropriation of trade secrets and infringement of intellectual property.

3. AUTHORIZED USE — STRICT RESTRICTIONS

   Even Authorized Personnel are subject to the following restrictions and may
   ONLY use the Software for the purpose explicitly authorized in their individual
   agreement with the Company. Except as expressly authorized in writing by the
   Company, you MAY NOT, directly or indirectly, whether personally or through
   any third party:

   a) REPRODUCTION & DISTRIBUTION: Copy, reproduce, duplicate, publish, upload,
      post, transmit, broadcast, distribute, or otherwise disseminate the Software
      or any portion thereof, in any form or by any means, electronic, mechanical,
      photocopying, recording, or otherwise.

   b) MODIFICATION: Modify, adapt, translate, localize, customize, enhance,
      extend, or create Derivative Works based on the Software or any portion
      thereof.

   c) REVERSE ENGINEERING: Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decode,
      decrypt, or attempt to derive or reconstruct the source code, underlying
      algorithms, data structures, ideas, or architecture of the Software.

   d) COMMERCIALIZATION: Sublicense, sell, resell, rent, lease, lend, time-share,
      transfer, assign, or otherwise commercially exploit or make available to any
      third party the Software or any rights therein.

   e) COMPETING USE: Use the Software, or any knowledge, information, or ideas
      derived therefrom, to develop, design, assist in the development of, or
      provide technical input to any Competing Product or service.

   f) DISCLOSURE: Disclose, share, communicate, demonstrate, or make available
      the Software or any Confidential Information derived therefrom to any third
      party, whether or not for compensation, without prior written consent from
      the Company.

   g) PROPRIETARY NOTICES: Remove, alter, obscure, cover, or modify any
      proprietary notices, copyright notices, trademarks, trade names, labels,
      watermarks, or marks on or within the Software.

   h) UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS: Access or use the Software for any purpose not
      explicitly authorized by the Company in writing.

   i) AUTOMATED PROCESSING & AI TRAINING: Use the Software, its source code,
      architecture, data models, or any portion thereof as training data, fine-
      tuning data, or input for any artificial intelligence, machine learning,
      large language model, neural network, or automated system of any kind,
      whether for commercial or non-commercial purposes.

   j) CIRCUMVENTION: Circumvent, disable, or otherwise interfere with any
      security features, access controls, license enforcement mechanisms, or
      technical protection measures incorporated in the Software.

   k) EXPORT: Export or re-export the Software in violation of any applicable
      export control laws or regulations of Mexico or any other jurisdiction.

   l) BENCHMARKING: Use the Software for benchmarking, competitive analysis, or
      performance testing for the benefit of any third party or Competing Product.

4. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY OWNERSHIP

   4.1 The Company retains all right, title, and interest in and to the Software
       and all intellectual property rights therein. Nothing in this Agreement
       shall be construed to grant any implied license or other rights to the
       Software. All rights not expressly granted herein (none) are reserved by
       the Company.

   4.2 The following are exclusively owned by the Company:

       - All source code, object code, compiled binaries, and build artifacts
       - All database schemas, migrations, stored procedures, and seed data
       - All UI/UX designs, wireframes, prototypes, design tokens, and brand assets
       - All business logic, algorithms, data models, and data structures
       - All documentation, specifications, technical materials, and ADRs
       - All Supabase Edge Functions, cloud infrastructure configurations
       - All API designs, integration patterns, and security architectures
       - All trademarks, trade names, logos, and service marks of MenuOS
       - All inventions, whether patentable or not, embodied in the Software
       - All improvements, enhancements, and modifications made by anyone

   4.3 Any work product, improvements, modifications, or Derivative Works created
       by Authorized Personnel in connection with the Software are works made for
       hire and shall be deemed assigned to and owned exclusively by the Company
       from the moment of creation, without any further act or compensation.

5. CONFIDENTIALITY

   5.1 The Software contains highly valuable trade secrets and Confidential
       Information of the Company. Authorized Personnel agree to:

       a) Maintain strict confidentiality of all Confidential Information;
       b) Use Confidential Information solely for purposes authorized by the
          Company;
       c) Not disclose Confidential Information to any third party without prior
          written consent;
       d) Apply no less than the highest standard of care to protect Confidential
          Information — in no case less than the care used to protect their own
          most sensitive confidential information;
       e) Promptly notify the Company upon discovering any unauthorized disclosure
          or use of Confidential Information;
       f) Return or destroy all copies of the Software upon termination of their
          authorized relationship with the Company.

   5.2 Confidentiality obligations survive the termination of any agreement or
       authorized relationship with the Company indefinitely.

6. NON-COMPETE

   Authorized Personnel who have had access to the Software agree that, for a
   period of two (2) years following the termination of their authorized
   relationship with the Company, they will not, directly or indirectly:

   a) Develop, co-develop, or provide technical consulting services for any
      Competing Product or service;
   b) Use knowledge, architecture, designs, or concepts derived from the Software
      to create or assist in creating any Competing Product;
   c) Solicit or induce any employee, contractor, or customer of the Company to
      terminate their relationship with the Company.

   The parties acknowledge that the restrictions in this Section are reasonable
   and necessary to protect the Company's legitimate business interests.

7. AUDIT RIGHTS

   The Company reserves the right, upon reasonable notice, to audit the systems
   and records of any Authorized Personnel or entity to verify compliance with
   this Agreement. Such audits shall be conducted at the Company's expense unless
   a material breach is discovered, in which case the breaching party shall bear
   all audit costs.

8. NO WARRANTIES

   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED SOLELY FOR USE BY AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL IN ACCORDANCE
   WITH THIS AGREEMENT. THE COMPANY MAKES NO WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF
   MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, OR
   NON-INFRINGEMENT. THE ENTIRE RISK AS TO THE QUALITY AND PERFORMANCE OF THE
   SOFTWARE RESTS WITH THE USER.

9. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY

   TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
   COMPANY OR ITS OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, OR AGENTS BE LIABLE FOR ANY
   INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES
   (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, LOSS OF PROFITS, LOSS OF DATA, BUSINESS
   INTERRUPTION, OR LOSS OF GOODWILL) ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE
   SOFTWARE OR THIS AGREEMENT, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH
   DAMAGES.

10. INJUNCTIVE RELIEF

    The parties acknowledge that any breach or threatened breach of this Agreement
    would cause irreparable harm to the Company for which monetary damages would
    be an inadequate remedy, and that the Company shall therefore be entitled, in
    addition to all other remedies available at law or in equity, to seek
    immediate injunctive and other equitable relief without the necessity of
    proving actual damages or posting any bond or other security.

11. REMEDIES FOR BREACH

    In the event of any unauthorized access to, use, reproduction, modification,
    distribution, or disclosure of the Software:

    a) All rights and permissions, if any, granted to the breaching party are
       immediately and automatically terminated without notice;
    b) The Company is entitled to seek all available legal and equitable remedies,
       including injunctive relief, actual damages, disgorgement of profits,
       statutory damages, and attorney's fees;
    c) The breaching party shall be liable for all costs and expenses (including
       legal fees) incurred by the Company in enforcing its rights;
    d) Civil liability under Mexican copyright law (Ley Federal del Derecho de
       Autor), trade secret law (Ley Federal de Protección a la Propiedad
       Industrial), and criminal liability under the Código Penal Federal may
       apply.

12. TERMINATION

    12.1 Any authorization granted to Authorized Personnel terminates automatically
         and immediately upon:

         a) Breach of any provision of this Agreement;
         b) Termination of the employment, contractor, or other authorized
            relationship with the Company;
         c) Written notice of termination by the Company for any reason.

    12.2 Upon termination, the Authorized Personnel must immediately:

         a) Cease all access to and use of the Software;
         b) Delete or destroy all copies of the Software in their possession
            or control;
         c) Certify in writing to the Company that all copies have been deleted
            or destroyed upon request.

    12.3 Sections 4, 5, 6, 9, 10, 11, 13, and 14 survive termination indefinitely.

13. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION

    13.1 This Agreement shall be governed by and construed exclusively in
         accordance with the laws of the United Mexican States (República
         Mexicana), specifically including:

         - Ley Federal del Derecho de Autor (LFDA)
         - Ley Federal de Protección a la Propiedad Industrial (LFPPI)
         - Código Civil Federal
         - Código de Comercio
         - Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los
           Particulares (LFPDPPP)

    13.2 Any dispute, controversy, or claim arising out of or relating to this
         Agreement, or the breach, termination, or validity thereof, shall be
         subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the federal courts (Tribunales
         de la Federación) located in Mexico City (Ciudad de México), Mexico.
         The parties hereby irrevocably waive any objection to such jurisdiction
         and venue.

    13.3 The prevailing party in any legal proceeding arising under this Agreement
         shall be entitled to recover its reasonable attorney's fees and costs from
         the non-prevailing party.

14. GENERAL PROVISIONS

    14.1 ENTIRE AGREEMENT: This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between
         the parties with respect to the Software and supersedes all prior or
         contemporaneous understandings, representations, or agreements, whether
         written or oral, regarding the subject matter hereof.

    14.2 SEVERABILITY: If any provision of this Agreement is held invalid,
         illegal, or unenforceable, such provision shall be modified to the
         minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, and the remaining
         provisions shall remain in full force and effect.

    14.3 NO WAIVER: The failure of the Company to enforce any right or provision
         of this Agreement shall not constitute a waiver of such right or provision.
         Any waiver must be in writing and signed by an authorized officer of the
         Company.

    14.4 AMENDMENT: This Agreement may only be amended by a written instrument
         signed by an authorized officer of the Company.

    14.5 ASSIGNMENT: This Agreement and any rights or obligations hereunder may
         not be assigned, transferred, or sublicensed by any Authorized Personnel
         without the prior written consent of the Company. The Company may freely
         assign this Agreement.

    14.6 NOTICES: All notices under this Agreement shall be in writing and
         delivered to the Company at: legal@menuos.mx

    14.7 HEADINGS: Section headings are for convenience only and shall not affect
         the interpretation of this Agreement.

